Hell, most of the time,
actually.

30:05.020 --> 30:07.011
But, brother,
you should know
when you with me,

30:07.060 --> 30:09.711
you can put that down,

30:11.540 --> 30:13.713
And I never
mean you any harm.

30:13.760 --> 30:16.365
Look here,
if you can't put it down,

30:16.420 --> 30:18.547
let me know that, too,

30:18.590 --> 30:21.206
and I'll carry it
with you.

30:21.250 --> 30:23.684
'Cause I know you'd do
the same thing for me.

30:24.910 --> 30:27.378
He flew into the sun

30:27.430 --> 30:30.251
Let's see
how long you run

30:30.300 --> 30:33.087
While you're hiding
from your soul...

30:33.130 --> 30:34.256
Love you, boy.

30:34.310 --> 30:35.732
Love you, too, dawg.

30:37.570 --> 30:39.959
- We're straight.
- All right.

30:40.010 --> 30:42.433
I'll see y'all
later.

30:45.140 --> 30:48.792
We can't have
your hands hurting.

30:48.840 --> 30:52.230
So I brought you
my go-tos.

30:52.280 --> 30:55.067
Take a chance
and find out...

30:55.110 --> 30:58.716
- And of course,
there's always this.
- Find out who you are...

31:01.860 --> 31:04.852
And let
your soul control

31:04.900 --> 31:07.721
Where you're going.

31:07.770 --> 31:10.819
- Shall we?
- No, it's for you.

31:10.860 --> 31:12.737
It's good medicine.

31:12.780 --> 31:15.908
Put yourself
in a warm bath
with those oils

31:15.960 --> 31:19.657
and relax your muscles
and your mind.

31:21.220 --> 31:25.839
This is
the best prescription
I've ever had.

31:25.880 --> 31:26.915
Do you know Lorna's
in town?

31:29.320 --> 31:32.096
Yes.

31:32.150 --> 31:34.880
I hope Charley don't
bring her around here.

31:34.930 --> 31:36.659
I've had enough
of that lately.

31:36.720 --> 31:38.881
Enough of what?

31:38.940 --> 31:41.454
White folks
up In my house.

31:41.500 --> 31:46.597
Holleood had one
of his co-workers in here.

31:46.640 --> 31:48.505
Just way too familiar.

31:48.550 --> 31:50.245
I don't want that.

31:50.290 --> 31:51.598
This is our house.

31:51.640 --> 31:53.904
My place
to feel comfortable.

31:53.950 --> 31:57.818
So did you not like
Lorna all these years
because she was white?

31:57.870 --> 32:03.388
Or 'cause of things
with her and Pops

32:03.440 --> 32:04.566
and Mom?

32:04.610 --> 32:06.214
Do I have to choose?

32:06.270 --> 32:08.830
I don't know, I--

32:08.880 --> 32:10.780
I just don't
care for her.

32:10.840 --> 32:12.569
I don't like the way
she conducts herself.

32:12.620 --> 32:15.180
How's that?

32:15.230 --> 32:19.269
Like...
she owned Ernest.

32:22.500 --> 32:25.719
I don't know,
like she thought
she was better than us.

32:25.760 --> 32:27.978
Did Mom feel that way?

32:28.030 --> 32:30.590
I don't know,
I guess.

32:30.640 --> 32:33.370
Aunt Vi,
I'm asking for real.

32:33.420 --> 32:37.333
How did Mom
feel about Lorna?

32:37.390 --> 32:41.030
Like, what happened?

32:41.080 --> 32:42.604
All these years,
I've been hatin' on her

32:42.650 --> 32:45.380
because
everybody else did.

32:45.440 --> 32:47.738
But what did she do?

32:47.790 --> 32:49.951
Did she break them up?

32:52.570 --> 32:54.265
It's complicated.

32:54.320 --> 32:57.221
No, she didn't
break them up,

32:57.270 --> 32:59.886
but she did stand in the way
of them getting back together.

32:59.930 --> 33:00.885
How?

33:03.060 --> 33:05.199
She interrupted
everything.

33:05.240 --> 33:09.028
Ernest was Trudy's,
and Trudy was Ernest's.

33:09.070 --> 33:10.719
Everybody knew that.

33:14.900 --> 33:17.152
And, okay, so your--

33:17.210 --> 33:20.168
your mama wanted
to explore and whatnot,

33:20.210 --> 33:23.031
but, still,
they had something unique,

33:23.080 --> 33:25.992
something
everybody wanted.

33:26.040 --> 33:28.349
And they was meant
to be together, period.

33:28.390 --> 33:30.915
Then comes Lorna.

33:30.960 --> 33:34.873
Did Mom break up with him
before he left for
California?

33:36.360 --> 33:38.316
Yeah, but...

33:40.490 --> 33:42.048
she didn't think
he was gonna go there

33:42.100 --> 33:44.625
and marry
a white lady.

33:44.670 --> 33:46.149
- Come on.
- FaIr enough.

33:46.190 --> 33:47.976
But did she deny him

33:48.020 --> 33:50.068
when he came back
to ask about me?

33:50.110 --> 33:51.065
[ sighs ]

33:52.810 --> 33:54.801
When she was pregnant
with me?

33:58.120 --> 34:00.247
Baby, she was young,

34:00.290 --> 34:02.246
and she wanted
things her way,

34:02.300 --> 34:05.997
so, yeah,
she turned him down.

34:06.040 --> 34:09.908
But she did not think
It was permanent.

34:09.960 --> 34:11.769
I know that.

34:11.830 --> 34:18.087
Then comes Lorna
and Charley and...

34:18.140 --> 34:22.053
it just got,
like I said, complicated.

34:24.190 --> 34:26.579
Where's all this
comIn' from?

34:28.970 --> 34:31.848
I just wanna know
what's real.

34:33.850 --> 34:35.886
I really had to think.

34:35.940 --> 34:39.194
Like, deep
in my memories,

34:39.250 --> 34:41.195
and I don't
remember Mom

34:41.250 --> 34:44.890
ever saying anything bad
about Lorna directly.

34:46.510 --> 34:50.071
I think I got this feeling
about her from you.

34:52.350 --> 34:54.648
And what's wrong
with that?

34:54.700 --> 34:59.342
Well, it's wrong

34:59.400 --> 35:01.618
because I don't know
who she is for myself.

35:03.620 --> 35:04.962
And I should.

35:10.580 --> 35:14.619
Probably a good idea
ifI make up my own mind.

35:17.590 --> 35:20.320
[ music playing ]

35:23.640 --> 35:24.937
Thank you, baby.

35:27.120 --> 35:30.339
I'm gonna go
take my bath.

35:34.170 --> 35:36.126
I am scared

35:37.480 --> 35:40.995
So I am human.

35:46.880 --> 35:49.132
[ music playing ]

35:59.940 --> 36:01.589
Hey, Charley.

36:03.330 --> 36:04.843
Hey, Lorna.

36:07.860 --> 36:10.545
I came by looking
for Charley.

36:11.640 --> 36:13.198
She will, uh,

36:13.250 --> 36:15.423
be back from the mill
in about an hour.

36:15.470 --> 36:18.428
We had dinner reservations
before I leave.

36:20.390 --> 36:22.176
Okay.

36:28.440 --> 36:30.135
Seeing you...

36:32.840 --> 36:35.741
Seeing you...

36:35.800 --> 36:39.019
makes me think about him
more than I want to
rIght now.

36:40.890 --> 36:43.108
Everything makes me
think about him.

36:43.150 --> 36:45.801
And I really can't even
believe that he's gone,

36:45.850 --> 36:48.717
because I've always
pictured him here

36:48.770 --> 36:52.854
on the land and happy.

36:52.900 --> 36:54.458
Home.

36:57.300 --> 36:59.029
I know.

36:59.080 --> 37:02.379
I really did love him.

37:06.440 --> 37:09.341
- I know that.
- And I never meant
to hurt anybody.

37:12.400 --> 37:16.393
Sometimes
we don't mean to,

37:16.450 --> 37:19.055
but it happens anyway.

37:20.840 --> 37:23.104
[ singers vocalizing ]

37:25.890 --> 37:27.585
That goes both ways.

37:28.810 --> 37:30.766
My faith

37:30.810 --> 37:36.339
My faith
don't mean a thing

37:39.120 --> 37:41.372
- Oh, my faith...
- [ door closes ]

37:41.430 --> 37:45.605
- My faith
don't mean a thing.
- [ sniffles ]

37:47.780 --> 37:49.691
- Ah!
- It's a terrible call.

37:49.740 --> 37:51.696
God!

37:51.740 --> 37:54.823
Never let me
place another bet
a day in my life, please.

37:54.880 --> 37:56.916
Good gracious,
I'm getting killed today.

37:56.970 --> 37:59.097
Will:
That is a terrible call.

37:59.140 --> 38:01.131
- Holleood, Roseman.
- What's up, boss man?

38:01.190 --> 38:02.225
